channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: What the 9 human cases of bird flu in the U.S. so far tell us about the disease
item.description: U.S. cases of bird flu have been relatively mild and limited to farm workers who handled sick animals – a sign the virus may not be well suited to infecting humans in its current state.

item.title: Three brutal Prince Harry and Meghan Markle snubs 'show tide is turning'
item.description: The Duke and Duchess of Sussex have faced a barrage of criticism in recent weeks, with commentators suggesting the tide may be turning in the US for the couple

item.title: 14 children end up in hospital after trying ‘adult only’ crisps
item.description: The 'R18' crisps are made using an extract from the ultra-spicy ghost pepper.

item.title: Democrats are banking on outperforming Biden in key Senate races
item.description: Democrats in tough races in the 2024 elections are hoping President Joe Biden's poll numbers after the debate won't hurt them in November.

item.title: Missing Brit Ben Ross fell victim to dark Majorca problem days before disappearing
item.description: Ben Ross, from Wigan, hasn't been heard from since falling victim to a theft on the Spanish island of Majorca – a problem that is all-too-common in the region

item.title: Woman describes out of body aura she felt in near-death experience after crash
item.description: 'The experience has allowed me to see the beauty of life.'

item.title: In states with strict abortion policies, simply seeing an OB/GYN for regular care can be difficult
item.description: States with strict abortion bans have worse health outcomes for pregnant women, according to a new report from the Commonwealth Fund.

item.title: Hidden gem beach in UK 'one of most beautiful places in the world'
item.description: The Warren, a stunning cove near Folkestone, boasts golden sands, chalk cliffs, and breathtaking sea views, yet remains peaceful even during the height of summer

item.title: Sheep start behaving strangely after eating 100kg of cannabis in greenhouse
item.description: The herd munched an entire crop of weed.

item.title: 2024 Olympics: Will the U.S. cruise to gold medals in track? Not if the Jamaicans have anything to say about it
item.description: There will be 206 countries represented at the 2024 Paris Olympics.

item.title: Warning people could be missing out on benefits as huge sums unclaimed
item.description: From one-off payments to Council Tax reductions, there is a wide range of financial support available that you might be eligible for - and you could get it in time for the summer holidays

item.title: Blind mystic Baba Vanga made a chilling prediction for 2025
item.description: 28 years after her death, Baba Vanga's predictions seem to be coming to fruition.

item.title: 30 years later, a 'push for justice' over Argentina's Jewish center bombing
item.description: On July 18, 1994, a van loaded with explosives crashed into a Jewish community center in Buenos Aires, killing 85 people at the Argentinian Israelite Mutual Association.

item.title: 'Cringe' book dedicated to Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce's relationship leaves fans divided
item.description: A Taylor Swift fan has received mixed feedback after dedicating her novel to the pop star and her NFL player boyfriend Travis Kelce, with many claiming the gesture is 'cringe' – while others say they 'love' the story

item.title: Man tries to smuggle 100 snakes in his trousers and it goes as you’d expect
item.description: He was trying to walk through the 'nothing to declare' gate when he was stopped.
